n <- length(c)
n
[1] 1178
t <- 1:n

# Change Detection
mymodel <- function() {
  # Data Come From A Gaussian
  for (i in 1:n){
    c[i] ~ dnorm(mu[z1[i]],lambda)
  }
  # Group Means
  mu[1] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  mu[2] ~ dnorm(0,.001)
  # Common Precision
  lambda  ~ dgamma(.001,.001)
  sigma  <- 1/sqrt(lambda)
  # Which Side is Time of Change Point?
  for (i in 1:n){
    z[i]  <- step(t[i]-tau) # step(x) x 0   1,  0
    z1[i] <- z[i]+1
  }
  # Prior On Change Point
  tau ~ dunif(0,n)     
}

samples <- jags(data = list(c = c, n = n, t = t),
                parameters.to.save = c("mu","sigma","tau"),
                inits = list(list(mu = c(1,1), lambda = 1, tau = n/2)),
                model.file = mymodel,
                n.chains = 1, n.iter = 10000, n.burnin = 1, n.thin = 1,
                jags.module = c("dic")
                )
